verses.text_plain: My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me? why art thou so far from helping me, and from the words of my roaring?
verses.verse_html:
1My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me? why art thou so far from helping me, and from the words of my roaring? ▼
▼ Aijeleth…: or, the hind of the morning
 , ▼
▼ helping…: Heb. my salvation

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Aijeleth…: or, the hind of the morning
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Aijeleth…: or, the hind of the morning
▼ helping…: Heb. my salvation

verses.text_plain: O my God, I cry in the daytime, but thou hearest not; and in the night season, and am not silent.
verses.verse_html:
2O my God, I cry in the daytime, but thou hearest not; and in the night season, and am not silent. ▼
▼ am…: Heb. there is no silence to me

tokens.text: not; and in the night season

footnotes.body_text: ▼ am…: Heb. there is no silence to me
footnotes.body_html: ▼ am…: Heb. there is no silence to me

verses.text_plain: But thou art holy, O thou that inhabitest the praises of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 3But thou art holy, O thou that inhabitest the praises of Israel.

verses.text_plain: Our fathers trusted in thee: they trusted, and thou didst deliver them.
verses.verse_html: 4Our fathers trusted in thee: they trusted, and thou didst deliver them.

verses.text_plain: They cried unto thee, and were delivered: they trusted in thee, and were not confounded.
verses.verse_html: 5They cried unto thee, and were delivered: they trusted in thee, and were not confounded.

tokens.text: in thee, and were not confounded

verses.text_plain: But I am a worm, and no man; a reproach of men, and despised of the people.
verses.verse_html: 6But I am a worm, and no man; a reproach of men, and despised of the people.

verses.text_plain: All they that see me laugh me to scorn: they shoot out the lip, they shake the head, saying,
verses.verse_html:
7All they that see me laugh me to scorn: they shoot out the lip, they shake the head, saying, ▼
▼ shoot…: Heb. open

verses.text_plain: He trusted on the Lord that he would deliver him: let him deliver him, seeing he delighted in him.
verses.verse_html:
8He trusted on the Lord that he would deliver him: let him deliver him, seeing he delighted in him. ▼
▼ He trusted…: Heb. He rolled himself on
 , ▼
▼ seeing…: or, if he delight in

footnotes.body_text: ▼ He trusted…: Heb. He rolled himself on
footnotes.body_html: ▼ He trusted…: Heb. He rolled himself on

footnotes.body_text: ▼ seeing…: or, if he delight in
footnotes.body_html: ▼ seeing…: or, if he delight in

verses.text_plain: But thou art he that took me out of the womb: thou didst make me hope when I was upon my mother’s breasts.
verses.verse_html:
9But thou art he that took me out of the womb: thou didst make me hope when I was upon my mother’s breasts. ▼
▼ didst…: or, kept me in safety

footnotes.body_text: ▼ didst…: or, kept me in safety
footnotes.body_html: ▼ didst…: or, kept me in safety

verses.text_plain: I was cast upon thee from the womb: thou art my God from my mother’s belly.
verses.verse_html: 10I was cast upon thee from the womb: thou art my God from my mother’s belly.

verses.text_plain: Be not far from me; for trouble is near; for there is none to help.
verses.verse_html:
11Be not far from me; for trouble is near; for there is none to help. ▼
▼ none…: Heb. not a helper

footnotes.body_html: ▼ none…: Heb. not a helper

verses.text_plain: Many bulls have compassed me: strong bulls of Bashan have beset me round.
verses.verse_html: 12Many bulls have compassed me: strong bulls of Bashan have beset me round.

verses.text_plain: They gaped upon me with their mouths, as a ravening and a roaring lion.
verses.verse_html:
13They gaped upon me with their mouths, as a ravening and a roaring lion. ▼
▼ gaped…: Heb. opened their mouths against me

footnotes.body_text: ▼ gaped…: Heb. opened their mouths against me
footnotes.body_html: ▼ gaped…: Heb. opened their mouths against me

verses.text_plain: I am poured out like water, and all my bones are out of joint: my heart is like wax; it is melted in the midst of my bowels.
verses.verse_html:
14I am poured out like water, and all my bones are out of joint: my heart is like wax; it is melted in the midst of my bowels. ▼
▼ out of…: or, sundered

footnotes.body_html: ▼ out of…: or, sundered

verses.text_plain: My strength is dried up like a potsherd; and my tongue cleaveth to my jaws; and thou hast brought me into the dust of death.
verses.verse_html: 15My strength is dried up like a potsherd; and my tongue cleaveth to my jaws; and thou hast brought me into the dust of death.

verses.text_plain: For dogs have compassed me: the assembly of the wicked have inclosed me: they pierced my hands and my feet.
verses.verse_html: 16For dogs have compassed me: the assembly of the wicked have inclosed me: they pierced my hands and my feet.

verses.text_plain: I may tell all my bones: they look and stare upon me.
verses.verse_html: 17I may tell all my bones: they look and stare upon me.

verses.text_plain: They part my garments among them, and cast lots upon my vesture.
verses.verse_html: 18They part my garments among them, and cast lots upon my vesture.

verses.text_plain: But be not thou far from me, O Lord: O my strength, haste thee to help me.
verses.verse_html: 19But be not thou far from me, O Lord: O my strength, haste thee to help me.

verses.text_plain: Deliver my soul from the sword; my darling from the power of the dog.
verses.verse_html:
20Deliver my soul from the sword; my darling from the power of the dog. ▼
▼ my darling: Heb. my only one
 , ▼
▼ power: Heb. hand

footnotes.body_text: ▼ my darling: Heb. my only one
footnotes.body_html: ▼ my darling: Heb. my only one

verses.text_plain: Save me from the lion’s mouth: for thou hast heard me from the horns of the unicorns.
verses.verse_html: 21Save me from the lion’s mouth: for thou hast heard me from the horns of the unicorns.

verses.text_plain: I will declare thy name unto my brethren: in the midst of the congregation will I praise thee.
verses.verse_html: 22I will declare thy name unto my brethren: in the midst of the congregation will I praise thee.

verses.text_plain: Ye that fear the Lord, praise him; all ye the seed of Jacob, glorify him; and fear him, all ye the seed of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 23Ye that fear the Lord, praise him; all ye the seed of Jacob, glorify him; and fear him, all ye the seed of Israel.

verses.text_plain: For he hath not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted; neither hath he hid his face from him; but when he cried unto him, he heard.
verses.verse_html: 24For he hath not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted; neither hath he hid his face from him; but when he cried unto him, he heard.

tokens.text: from him; but when he cried

verses.text_plain: My praise shall be of thee in the great congregation: I will pay my vows before them that fear him.
verses.verse_html: 25My praise shall be of thee in the great congregation: I will pay my vows before them that fear him.

verses.text_plain: The meek shall eat and be satisfied: they shall praise the Lord that seek him: your heart shall live for ever.
verses.verse_html: 26The meek shall eat and be satisfied: they shall praise the Lord that seek him: your heart shall live for ever.

verses.text_plain: All the ends of the world shall remember and turn unto the Lord: and all the kindreds of the nations shall worship before thee.
verses.verse_html: 27All the ends of the world shall remember and turn unto the Lord: and all the kindreds of the nations shall worship before thee.

verses.text_plain: For the kingdom is the Lord’s: and he is the governor among the nations.
verses.verse_html: 28For the kingdom is the Lord’s: and he is the governor among the nations.

verses.text_plain: All they that be fat upon earth shall eat and worship: all they that go down to the dust shall bow before him: and none can keep alive his own soul.
verses.verse_html: 29All they that be fat upon earth shall eat and worship: all they that go down to the dust shall bow before him: and none can keep alive his own soul.

tokens.text: him: and none can keep alive

verses.text_plain: A seed shall serve him; it shall be accounted to the Lord for a generation.
verses.verse_html: 30A seed shall serve him; it shall be accounted to the Lord for a generation.

verses.text_plain: They shall come, and shall declare his righteousness unto a people that shall be born, that he hath done this.
verses.verse_html: 31They shall come, and shall declare his righteousness unto a people that shall be born, that he hath done this.
